message: "If you use SkillForge in your research or workflows, please cite it as below."
type: software
title: "SkillForge: Semantic Document Compiler and AI Skill Toolkit"
authors:
  - family-names: Chen
    given-names: Liqun
url: "https://github.com/LiqunChen0606/skillforge"
repository-code: "https://github.com/LiqunChen0606/skillforge"
license: Apache-2.0
version: 0.1.0
date-released: "2026-04-02"
abstract: >-
  SkillForge is a semantic document compiler and AI skill toolkit built
  on the AIF (AI-native Interchange Format). Compiles typed documents to
  12+ formats with the best structure-per-token ratio: full semantic types
  at 22% fewer tokens than Markdown. Skills in LML format improve LLM
  compliance by 10 percentage points vs raw Markdown. Includes document
  cleaning/normalization for HTML, PDF, and Markdown; typed skill authoring
  with versioning and eval pipelines; and a codebase migration engine with
  LLM-powered verification and repair.
keywords:
  - llm
  - semantic-format
  - document-compiler
  - skill-authoring
  - token-efficiency
  - ai-native
